    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220\u00b0C/ 200\u00b0C (fan)/ gas 7 and boil a kettle</p><p>Take your <strong>chicken</strong> out of the fridge, open the packet and let it air</p><p>Add your <strong>basmati rice</strong> and <strong>cauliflower rice</strong> to an <strong>oven-proof dish</strong> with 120ml<span class=\"text-purple\"> [225ml]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [300ml] </span><strong>boiled water</strong></p><p>Cover tightly with <strong>tin foil</strong> and put the dish in the oven for 25-30 min or until all the water is absorbed and the rice is cooked \u2013 this is your <strong>baked cauliflower rice</strong></p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/honey-chicken-with-tomato-and-pepper-cauliflower-rice-bake/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Peel and finely dice your <strong>red onion[s]</strong></p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Dice your<strong> tomato[es]</strong></p><p>Deseed your <strong>pepper[s]<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span></strong>(scrape the seeds and pith out with a teaspoon) and dice</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/honey-chicken-with-tomato-and-pepper-cauliflower-rice-bake/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Chop your <strong>parsley </strong>roughly, including the stalks</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/honey-chicken-with-tomato-and-pepper-cauliflower-rice-bake/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil </strong>over a high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the<strong> diced onion </strong>with the <strong>diced pepper</strong>,<strong> diced tomato</strong>,<strong> half </strong>the <strong>chopped garlic </strong>and<strong> half</strong> your <strong>ground smoked paprika </strong>(you'll use the rest later!),<strong> tomato paste </strong>and<strong> chicken stock mix</strong></p><p>Add a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong>, give everything a good mix up and<strong> </strong>cook for 4-5 min or until slightly softened \u2013 this is your<strong> tomato & pepper mixture</strong></p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/honey-chicken-with-tomato-and-pepper-cauliflower-rice-bake/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>After the initial 10 min, remove the dish from the oven and stir through the <strong>tomato & pepper mixture</strong>, reserve the pan</p><p>Re-cover the dish with the tin foil and return it to the oven for a final 15-20 min \u2013 this is your<strong> tomato & pepper rice</strong></p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/honey-chicken-with-tomato-and-pepper-cauliflower-rice-bake/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>While the rice is in the oven, cover your <strong>chicken</strong> with <strong>cling film</strong> and bash with a <strong>rolling pin</strong> until it's an even thickness (not too thin!), then season with a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Wipe the reserved pan clean and return it to a medium-high heat with a drizzle of<strong> olive oil </strong>and once hot, add the <strong>flattened chicken</strong> and cook for 8 min on each side until browned</p><p>Once browned, drizzle over your <strong>honey</strong> and cook for a final 2-3 min or until glazed and cooked through (no pink meat!) \u2013 this is your<strong> honey chicken</strong></p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/honey-chicken-with-tomato-and-pepper-cauliflower-rice-bake/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, combine the <strong>remaining ground</strong> <strong>smoked paprika</strong>, <strong>remaining chopped garlic</strong> and the juice of <strong>half</strong> your<strong> lemon[s]</strong> in a bowl with 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [2 tbsp] </span><strong>olive oil </strong>and a generous pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and <strong>pepper </strong>\u2013 this is your <strong>smoky garlic dressing</strong></p><p>Cut the <strong>remaining</strong> <strong>lemon</strong> into 1 wedge per person</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/honey-chicken-with-tomato-and-pepper-cauliflower-rice-bake/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Slice the <strong>honey</strong> <strong>chicken</strong> thinly on a clean board</p><p>Serve the <strong>tomato &</strong> <strong>pepper cauliflower rice</strong> in a bowl topped with the <strong>sliced honey chicken</strong>, then<strong> </strong>sprinkle over the <strong>chopped parsley</strong> and drizzle over the <strong>smoky garlic dressing</strong></p><p><strong><span class=\"text-danger\">Tip: Cooking for kids? Leave out the parsley and smoky sauce, or just add a little!</span></strong></p><p>Garnish with a <strong>lemon wedge</strong> and enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
